# Logging Standards Guidelines

## Overview
This document outlines best practices and standards for logging within the Cursor project. It aims to ensure consistent, informative, and useful logging across all modules and agents.

## Best Practices
- Use standardized logging formats and templates.
- Log errors, warnings, and informational messages consistently.
- Include timestamps, log levels, and relevant context in each log entry.
- Rotate logs regularly to prevent storage issues.
- Ensure logs are accessible for debugging and auditing purposes.

## Implementation
- Use a centralized logging system if possible.
- Integrate logging frameworks that support configuration management and scalability.
- Maintain clear documentation on logging practices and updates.